==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: stare
<hw>stare</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>stared</conjf> <pr>(st⟦acir⟧rd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>staring</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[AS. <ets>starian</ets>; akin to
LG. & D. <ets>staren</ets>, OHG. <ets>star⟦emac⟧n</ets>, G.
<ets>starren</ets>, Icel. <ets>stara</ets>; cf. Icel. <ets>stira</ets>,
Dan. <ets>stirre</ets>, Sw. <ets>stirra</ets>, and G. <ets>starr</ets>
stiff, rigid, fixed, Gr. <grk>stereo`s</grk> solid (E.
<ets>stereo-</ets>), Skr. <ets>sthira</ets> firm, strong. ⟦root⟧166. Cf.
<er>Sterile</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To look with fixed eyes wide
open, as through fear, wonder, surprise, impudence, etc.; to fasten an
earnest and prolonged gaze on some object.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For ever upon the ground I see thee <qex>stare</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Look not big, nor stamp, nor <qex>stare</qex>, nor fret.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To be very conspicuous on account of size,
prominence, color, or brilliancy; <as>as, <ex>staring</ex> windows or
colors</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To stand out; to project; to bristle.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Makest my blood cold, and my hair to <qex>stare</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Take off all the <qex>staring</qex> straws and jags in the
hive.</q> <rj><qau>Mortimer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To gaze; to look earnestly. See
<er>Gaze</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stare</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Stare
<hw>Stare</hw> <pr>(st⟦acir⟧r)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To look
earnestly at; to gaze at.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I will <qex>stare</qex> him out of his wits.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To stare in the face</b></col>, <cd>to be before the
eyes, or to be undeniably evident.</cd> ⟦ldquo⟧The law . . .
<xex>stares</xex> them <xex>in the face</xex> whilst they are breaking
it.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Locke.</au></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stare</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Stare
<hw>Stare</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of staring; a fixed look with
eyes wide open.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A dull and stupid <xex>stare</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Churchill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Starer</ent>⟦br⟧
